parameters:
Boss: Alright, you guys. Make sure to do the KYT
finger-pointing confirmation and checklist on your
own. Prioritize compliance, not just completing
it.

Young person: Sigh... It's so blissful to be able
to just laze around without doing anything...

Red-haired worker: Boss, you don't usually say
things like that... Are you coming for the
headquarters inspection?

Do you need something... Ah! You dropped these
documents the other day...!

Salaryman: Yes, I appreciate your help the other
day! Thanks to you, I feel a bit better!
(hesitant)
Oh no, it was just a small favor.

Salaryman: Well... It's been a while since someone
has been kind to me, so I'm really happy...

(By the way... When Rei-san sensed someone in
distress, this person came...)

(I wonder if I'm causing this gloomy atmosphere...
If that's the case, maybe I should listen to their
story...)

Salaryman: Ah! It's already this late... Well
then, I'll go back to work... *sigh* See you
later...

Um...! If it's okay, would you like to talk a
little more?

Salaryman: Uh... B-but, it's been 4 minutes since
my break started, so I should probably go back...
I-I want to talk a little more with you...

I see... So many people suddenly quit, and that's
why you're burdened with the workload...

Salaryman: Uh... I never thought I would have to
do sales, accounting, HR, and production all at
the same time...

Salaryman: H-However, recently there are times
when I can finish work by 10 PM, and there are
many occasions where I only have to work until 2
AM. Compared to before, it has gotten better!

(This person... how are they surviving with
that...)

Salaryman: Well... It would be easier if there was
someone who could at least handle the sales as a
temporary measure...

Salaryman: Eh!? W-Well... but, you see... it's not
easy to suddenly handle sales without some
experience...

Don't worry. In the past, I worked at a company
called Kawayama Shoji and another company called
Ichiba Shoji, where I handled everything from
sales to accounting.

Salaryman: Wha...?! You, you worked at such big
companies...!? \.P-Please, I beg you!! I'll inform
the company about it!

Salaryman: Well then, I will explain the detailed
job description when you come to our company!

(Sometimes my past experience comes in handy.
Well, I should get my suit cleaned.)

Mohican Worker: Complah...? Are you talking about
tempura made from daikon radish?

Male on break: Sigh... Haa... I better take this
opportunity to relieve some stress...

Horny Man: Ah, damn... I'm so horny... I wish
there was a stupid woman who would sleep with me
right away...

Today's recommended\c[6]\c[0] Manager's
Specialty Roasted Espresso\c[6]\c[0]

Today's recommendation is Ayako Nagatsuki's
homemade milk coffee. Limited to 10 servings per
day.

Today's recommendation is Ayako Nagatsuki's
homemade milk coffee.

Male: Children are adorable, aren't they? When I
see their innocent smiles, it makes me smile too.

Male: Well, sometimes I get flustered by words
that are too honest.

Girl: Wow, Auntie! Your breasts are bigger than
Mom's!

(Lately, it feels like my bra has been getting
tighter... Could it be... that I've gained
weight?!)

A man taking a break says, Phew... I can't smoke
in the office, so I'll take this opportunity to
stock up on cigarettes.

A man relieving himself, Phew.... *trickling
sound*

(Huh, huh.... So it's okay to do this kind of
thing here...)

(Ah... I can see a penis through the gap between
their legs... )

Angry man on the phone: Takeda!!! I told you to
leave it in front of the warehouse, not right in
front of the entrance, you idiot!!

Man: Excuse me, madam. Are you injured... \.
Hmm...

Yes, I'm fine. Despite appearances, I move my body
quite a lot.
Man: I see... No wonder it's top-notch...

Man: Oh, by the way, we recently started offering
a special milk coffee at this shop.

Man: If you tell the master that you're an
acquaintance of 'Sonomori', they might give you
special service. Please give it a try.
Really! Is that okay? Thank you very much
Man: Hehehe... No, the pleasure is all mine...
Man: Well then, I'll take my leave.

Lucky  With this, I can drink delicious coffee
for free.

Is that person the owner? They have such a dandy
voice and seem so kind...

...Hm, have we met somewhere before? Well,
whatever. Coffee, coffee

The brown-haired salaryman muttered, Damn it...
that piece of junk broke again! It's about time to
get rid of it and buy a replacement!
The sunlight is so strong... I feel dizzy...
Boss: Hey hey hey, are you okay?
I'm sorry... I got a little dizzy.

Boss: Whoa... Those are huge tits!! And your face
is so damn cute...! *gulp*

Um... I'm sorry for being presumptuous, but could
I have some water...?

Boss: O-Oh, oh, alright! Sounds good...! Let's
take a break now and cool off for a bit!

Thank you very much. If it's alright with you,
could you please show me around...?
I'll take a break with you too...

After the event ends, if you press the Q key, you
can hear Ayako's soliloquy about that event.

Basically, it doesn't affect the game progress if
you don't listen to it, but she might whisper
something that could lead to hints for capturing.

Also, be aware that if you fall asleep at home or
listen to the event-related soliloquy
once,\c[2]she won't whisper it again.\c[0] So
please be careful if you want to hear all the
conversations.
